      "comment": "CAKE IN TUMMY (8) flew the lids with a fast early split last time, hitting the frame with a 3.5 lengths third (16.38) over 275m at this track and making it two placings on end. Makes plenty of appeal. FEARLESS TWO (3) turned in a better run last time to find a minor placing (17.78) at Northam behind Nitro Ned in a Grade 6. Has the early speed to land on the pace and can stick on. Leading chance. MIDNIGHT CRAVE (1) had to overcome a collision with another runner and could manage only a distant seventh (17.27) in a Grade 6 over 275m at this track. Better than last start and can bounce back. MAYDAY MAYDAY (6) was out of the money here last time out but can bounce back.",
